Next pull is past drop off, hang a right, follow the hall around to the left and straight back to the port pad (puller will again need groundspawn key - talon, under the table at far end of the first hall). Have epic wizzies duck into the rooms along the way and make sure you got everything. again about 18 or so mobs.<br><br>We havent ever figured out the key to South wing =\ but there is a pull pattern there as well, check out the maps available. Generally works the same way, pick a rush spot and head there.<br><br>Good luck and have fun!<br><br>Malagis(x) Windrider<br>AE Prophet of Gnomallah<br>58 Evoker<br>Officer of The Hand<br>Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udunroamin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunroamin1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/02 6:26:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Post deleted - see next post</span><hr size=1> (This message was left blank) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udunroamin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunroamin1</A> at: 1/22/02 8:38:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udunroamin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunroamin1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/02 6:32:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> HS rocks for AE - here's the scoop</span><hr size=1> HS is my favourite AE zone. There's usually no-one there, except maybe in the South wing, the mobs have low hp, and the pulls are pretty easy BUT you NEED a puller with a DA type ability to absorb the HTs.<br><br>My usual setup is this:<br>3 wizzies (2 high levels with the better jylls spells + a mage or drood works fine too if you can't find enough wizzies)<br>1 chanter with good connection.<br>1 cleric with balls of steel<br>1 puller with DA type ability, ideally paladin, level 60 bard (think they get DA song, don't quote me on this), or another cleric. <br><br>The basic idea is that the cleric and the puller will do the pulling for you - clerics get 2 DA type spells on 15 minutes refresh, pallies get one, giving you 1 pull every 5 mins or so. As 3 pulls will clear a wing, this is plenty. The first golem pull is easy, just pull the whole first room except the east wing ones ( there's a pit there). No DA needed for this pull. You then need a north wing key, tallow marked candle, which drops from the sperms, so if you haven't got one yet you'll need to drop down into the pit below the entrance area and get some sperms. Go into the north wing, and for the next pull send a puller with DA to grab the 4 before the picture, drop down, grab some more beyond the picture, and return to just below the picture. The rest of the group jumps thru the picture about 5 secs after the puller has jumped thru, to make sure the puller soaks up the HTs. The previous post gives a good guide to pull spots, now I come to read it properly.<br><br>It's basically the same kind of idea from then on. The important thing is to plan each pull. Either the puller runs back to the spot you have just cleared to, or you agree a &quot;ground zero&quot; point, which the puller will bring stuff to, and the rest will move to a few seconds after the puller has started his run and the way is clear.<br><br>If you don't know HS, there are very good maps around, which help a lot - I think spar's map of HS is best, but I don't have the URL to hand. The safehouse has a very good list of where the no rent keys to the various doors are - mostly ground spawns - which you will need as you have no rogue.<br><br>You can clear the north and west wings in 3 pulls each once you get the pull spots sorted.<br><br>The key to good AE in HS is a cleric who is willing to pull imo - these are pretty hard to come by.<br><br>If you get a regular group going, make sure you stash all your no rent keys in a bag, and get duelled at a wiz spire before you log. Loot all but the key bag from the corpse, and you can pick it up next time you log in, so you don't have to keep starting at the north wing. Duel the corpse a little way from the wiz spire or you'll get spammed by people offering you resses <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>One of these days I'll mark the pull spots on a map, and try to download my HS screenshots - 15 mobs can be done pretty regularly.<br><br>One variation would be to use a necro with harmshield as the puller. The advantage here is that the necro can duel a corpse with some coffins on it at the zone in, just in case the worst happens. I confess I only tried this once, and due to the necros pulling inexperience it didn't work out so well. Personally, I greatly favour pallies as the non-cleric puller. They tend to love pulling trains, and are great for meleeing down the last mob or two of a pull while the wizzies med up.<br><br>CR is, of course, a real bummer if you wipe out. This is only likely if you get major LDs - I've only ever had wipeouts there due to connection problems, and then very rarely indeed.<br><br>XP is awesome, even for an AE group, due to the low mob HP, low resists, and high zone xp mod.<br><br>It definitely helps peoples confidence if you have access to friends with CR capable chars - rogues, necros, clerics etc. Also, make people bind outside. As I say, I have almost never had a wipeout doing AE in HS, but the odd casualty does occur, usually through LDs.<br><br>Although having the cleric pull sounds crazy, remember that he doesn't actually do any damage to the mobs, so as soon as the stuns and nukes fly, he won't be getting aggro.<br><br><br><br>In summary:<br><br>Good things:<br>- uncrowded dungeon<br>- amazing xp<br>- easy to do good xp pulls<br>- nice loots possible<br>- fun fun fun fun fun<br><br>Bad things:<br>- CR very ugly if you wipe out.<br>- Getting keys can be a pain in the behind<br>- Quite a few green mobs to 60 in the easilly accessible wings (still great xp though)<br>- Finding a cleric willing to pull can be tough.<br><br>Enjoy!<br><br>Dunroamin<br>Sorceror on Sabbatical<br>Antonious Bayle (formerly Innoruuk) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udunroamin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunroamin1</A> at: 1/22/02 8:39:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urindindin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rindindin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 6:55:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grrr, couldn't edit last post, this is the correct versi</span><hr size=1> Hello Wizard Community,<br><br>i have a regular AOE Exp Group (Bard 60, Enc 57,60, Cleric 60, Wiz 60,57) and as sebelis is getting more and more crowded (lvl 60 need exp again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) i wanted to try HS as it is always empty on our server.<br>So far i know the problem are the HT i will get as puller - i am a lvl 60 bard with 18 secs DA song. So i would lik